"n.巫术，魔法 【英】 n.巫术，魔法(the use of evil magical power) 【记】 sorc(巫术)＋ery; 【同】 同根词：exorcise(用 魔法驱邪) n. 巫术(通过鬼神的帮助而使用超自然的力量) = witchcraft 【记】s, orc魔鬼, ery－魔法 【参】exorcise(v 驱邪; 除怪)ex出, orc魔鬼, ise 【记】soccer 足球是魔法，人看了就跟中了魔一样被吸引且兴奋地大喊大叫 sorcery (n.)  c.1300, from Old French sorcerie, from sorcier ""sorcerer, wizard,"" from Medieval Latin sortiarius ""teller of fortunes by lot; sorcerer,"" literally ""one who influences fate or fortune,"" from Latin sors (genitive sortis) ""lot, fate, fortune"" (see sort (n.))."
